sub_fields.label: Mutation Catalog
sub_fields.name: ue_mutation_catalog
sub_fields.instructions: List of all available process mutations

sub_fields.label: Input Field
sub_fields.name: ue_mutation_input_select
sub_fields.instructions: The field in the record you want to use as the source. You can use -> arrow terms to dig deeper into an array value if required. videoId->0 would reference the post's `videoId` field and the '0' key in that array.

sub_fields.label: Process Method
sub_fields.name: ue_process_method
sub_fields.instructions: The process will normally loop through the collection, then each record, and then each field. However, sometimes, you only want to perform a task once on the entire collection and copy the results onto each record.

sub_fields.label: Input Field

sub_fields.instructions: The field in the record you want to use as the source. NOTE - Only the fields that have been processed are available.

sub_fields.label: Combine Method
sub_fields.name: ue_combine_method
sub_fields.instructions: How to combine the records into one. The fields are "flattened" from arrays into single fields so each record is prefixed with the record number and identifiable. You can then use any field in the mapping section.

sub_fields.label: Posts
sub_fields.message:
Required Fields:

- post_content
- post_status = published

sub_fields.label: Meta
sub_fields.message:
Meta fields will always have an array as a value.
A field 'videoId' will become videoId[0] = 'value'.

sub_fields.label: Image
sub_fields.message:
An image is an 'attachment' post type and has the same fields as a post.
Required Fields:
- path (the wp-content/uploads... location)

sub_fields.label: YouTube Video Code

sub_fields.label: Video Seek Duration
sub_fields.name: video_seek_duration
sub_fields.instructions: The [hh:mm:ss] of how much (from the starting seek point) you want to download.

sub_fields.message: This mutation is "collection" processing enabled. Meaning that you only have to run it once on the entire collection, rather than multiple times for each record. Switch the field "Processing Method" to "Process entire collection once." to enable this feature. This will take all records {{collection}} and run multiple FFMpeg steps on those records. Each input record can be referenced in the script with $0, $1, $2, etc... $concate_file is present, it will create a new concat_file.txt that contains a list of all the video files in the collection. This can be used to have multiple inputs into FFMpeg. $inputs Will create a list of "-i input1.mp4 -i input2.mp4 -i input3.mp4..." $upload_dir Is the location of the current upload directory. Use for output file.

sub_fields.label: FFMpeg Arguments
sub_fields.name: ffmpeg_arguments
sub_fields.instructions: These are just the arguments to FFMPeg, They will. be prefixed with '/usr/local/ffmpeg'.
